<HEADLINE>
FT  31 DEC 92 / UK Company News: Receivers appointed at Beverley arm
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Beverley Group, the engineering concern formerly known as Petrocon, has
announced the appointment of receivers at Clydebank Engineering, a
wholly-owned subsidiary.
The remaining companies in the group continued to trade normally, the
directors said.
The company is also disposing of its Gorseline subsidiary to management for
Pounds 1.47m.
The proceeds of the sale would be used to reduce group borrowings, the
directors said.
</TEXT>
