<HEADLINE>
FT  31 DEC 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Christmas and new year holidays inevitably keep the market at a virtual
standstill. There are no wool sales and most textile producers are closed in
the UK till next week. A subdued close to the wool selling season in
Australia provided no incentive to trade buyers at the manufacturing end of
the industry, though early reports do indicate encouraging consumer demand
for clothing over the important Christmas season. Currency markets are not
fully tested but further strength in the US dollar is already a feature and
enhances wool costs in many wool-using countries.
