<HEADLINE>
FT  31 DEC 92 / World Commodities Prices: Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COFFEE futures came under heavy pressure at the London Futures and Options
Exchange yesterday in to continued speculative and investment fund
liquidation in New York. The March delivery position ended Dollars 25 down
at Dollars 1,010 a tonne and dealers said there might be scope for further
losses in the short term. But they thought the market's constructive
fundamentals would prompt a recovery in the new year. COCOA prices were also
lower but the market remained near the upper end of its recent trading
range. As the March futures price closed Pounds 5 lower at Pounds 693 a
tonne dealers said that it continued to run into upside resistance in the
Pounds 700 area, while key support remained at Pounds 657. Trading remained
routine at the London Metal Exchange. NICKEL recovered Tuesday's slippage
but was unable to erode resistance above Dollars 5,900 a tonne for three
months metal. LEAD lacked follow through to Tuesday's advance and the three
months price fell Pounds 5.25 to Pounds 300.75 a tonne.
Compiled from Reuters
</TEXT>
