THE GOVERNMENT'S deter-mination to continue with controversial changes to
healthcare provision in London was reiterated yesterday by Mrs Virginia
Bottomley, the health secretary, Alan Pike writes.
Mrs Bottomley says in a newsletter distributed to all National Health
Service staff in the capital that change can no longer be postponed.
She says in the publication that London's problems have been discussed for
years and too little has happened.
