number of hospital beds, closing or amalgamating famous hospitals and
shifting resources to family doctors and community services.
Mrs Bottomley is facing intense opposition to some of the proposed closures.
The report's recommendations include closing St Bartholomew's in the City;
amalgamating Guy's and St Thomas' on a single site; merging the Middlesex
and University College on the latter's site and moving the Royal Brompton
and Royal Marsden specialist hospitals to the Charing Cross site in west
London.
