<HEADLINE>
FT  29 DEC 92 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Most markets felt quiet due to coming holidays. Cassia/cinnamom: nearby
positions tight, demand small. Nutmegs/mace spot unchanged, shipment weak.
Ginger: New crop is declining. Although the harvest is widely expected to be
considerably less than last year, local and export demand have been soft.
This could turn around quickly. Spots are small and will not cushion the
trade. Cloves: Brazilian crop is in full swing, however crop shall be below
normal. Pimento: both Jamaican and Mexico spot europe very tight. Tendency
firm.
</TEXT>
