FT  29 DEC 92 / Tapie makes political comeback
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN and REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR Bernard Tapie, the flamboyant French politician and businessman, has
staged an astonishing end-of-year comeback by regaining the cabinet post he
lost earlier this year because of his involvement in a fraud case.
Mr Tapie has been re-appointed minister of towns, a post he held for seven
weeks before being forced to resign in May pending the fraud trial. The case
brought against him by Mr Georges Tranchant, the opposition politician who
was once a business partner, was dismissed last week, paving the way for his
return.
A public prosecutor has asked for corruption charges against Mr Francois
Leotard, a former culture minister, to be dropped, his lawyer said
yesterday, Reuter reports from Paris. Mr Leotard was indicted on charges of
buying a Riviera mansion at a knock-down price in return for municipal
contracts.
